            <description><![CDATA[
                <p>We&#39;ve got a couple short talks scheduled for this month, and we&#39;ve got
a new venue, generously provided by <a href="http://www.servercentral.com">ServerCentral</a>.</p>

<p><a href="http://metacpan.org/author/JBERGER">Joel Berger</a> is going to give
a talk on testing any <a href="http://plackperl.org">PSGI application</a> with
<a href="http://mojolicio.us/perldoc/Test/Mojo">Test::Mojo, Mojolicious&#39;s excellent web testing
library.</a></p>

<p>And, <a href="http://metacpan.org/author/PREACTION">Doug Bell</a> is going to give
a talk on some simple websocket tricks with <a href="http://metacpan.org/pod/mercury">Mercury, a WebSocket
message broker</a>, <a href="http://mojolicio.us">Mojolicious</a>
and <a href="http://mojolicio.us/perldoc/Mojo/UserAgent">Mojo::UserAgent</a>.</p>

<p>Due to the holidays, our meeting will be on December 10. <a href="http://www.meetup.com/ChicagoPM/events/226879320/">RSVP on the
Chicago.PM Meetup</a></p>

<p>(EDIT: Slides from the <a href="http://preaction.github.io/Stupid-Websocket-Tricks-With-Perl/">simple WebSocket tricks talk are now
available</a>)</p>

